This paper discusses techniques for disclosure limitation in microdata releases, which is a topic related to data privacy and security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases), which deals with data management and privacy. The paper also proposes algorithms for generating anonymous data sets, which involves machine learning and data mining techniques, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another likely category. The paper also discusses the utility preservation of the data sets, which is related to machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category. The algorithms proposed in the paper involve perturbing the data, which is related to data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another possible category. Finally, the paper also discusses the mathematical properties of the algorithms, which is related to information theory and coding, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category as well.
